s captivating, sometimes funny, sometimes heartbreaking narrative. She describes how clubs and restaurants pay promoters to recruit beautiful young women to their venues in order to attract men and get them to spend huge sums in the ritual of bottle service. These "girls" enhance the status of the men and enrich club owners, exchanging their bodily capital for as little as free drinks and a chance to party with men who are rich or aspire to be. Though they are priceless assets in the party circuit, these women are regarded as worthless as long-term relationship prospects, and their bodies are constantly assessed against men's money.A story of extreme gender inequality in a seductive world, Very Important People unveils troubling realities behind moneyed leisure in an age of record economic disparity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aBusinessmenxSocial life and customs. 0aRich people. 0aSocial status. 0aSocialites. 0aSubculture. 0aYoung womenxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Classes & Economic Disparity.2bisacsh  aDJ.  aDJs.  aPrimates of Park Avenue.  aRich Kids Instagram.  aTheory of the Leisure Class.  aThorstein Veblen.  aVIP area.  aVIP lifestyle.  aWednesday Martin.  aanthropology.  abanker bros.  abouncers.  abusiness men.  aclub promoter.  aclub promoters.  aclub scene.  aconspicuous consumption.  agirl capital.  ainequality.  asexism.  asexual exploitation.  asexual trafficking.  asuper rich.  atoxic masculinity.  atrafficking women.  aurban nightlife.  avelvet rope.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAG